race.comment: Is today the day BEAUTIFUL JEWEL (1) can break through again? It's been a while between drinks and she's been freshened up for this but it looks a very suitable assignment. If she can replicate her last start placing in a stronger race then she will win. She's versatile and can take up a forward spot if required. SEA OF LIGHTS (5) might be ready to peak third-up to 1550m and looks a danger. She's only won two races but she's always hinted that there is more there. ISUSPECTJEU (4) is on the quick back-up after running well at this track and distance last week. She's got no weight and maps well. FAST TEMPO (2) can run a cheeky race if she rolls forward and doesn't have to cop too much pressure.
